This is actually a documentation bug. When I converted a WMF file to SVG the
output contained <?xml... encoding="UTF-8"?>. However, there were incorrectly
coded characters in the generated file, so it was not readable by the
rasterizer, for instance.

The example in the WMFTranscoder class comment should be changed to use a Writer
for the output, like this:

FileOutputStream fos = new FileOutputStream(svgFile);
TranscoderOutput svg =
  new TranscoderOutput(new OutputStreamWriter(fos, "UTF-8"));

This ensures the output really is encoded the intended way.
